( BW)(TX-INDUSTRIAL-INFO-RES) American National Power Is Adding
1,395MW to Texas Grid, in an Advisory by Industrialinfo.com

    Business/Energy Editors

	   HOUSTON--(BUSINESS WIRE)--Nov. 26, 2001--Researched by
Industrialinfo.com (Industrial Information Resources Inc.; Houston).
American National Power Company (Houston), a wholly owned subsidiary
of International Power plc (LSE:IPR)(NYSE:IPR) (London), is in the
process of adding 550 mega-watt (MW) units number 5 and 6 at its
Midlothian II station in Midlothian, Texas, and a 275MW unit number 2
at Hays station in San Marcos, Texas, are all scheduled to come
on-line in the fourth quarter of 2001. Hays 570MW units number 3 and 4
are scheduled to follow in the first quarter of 2002.
	   Alstom Power (Midlothian, Va.) is the turn-key vendor/contractor
for both of these projects, which are utilizing Alstom's ABB GT24
natural gas-fired combustion turbine/generator sets in combined-cycle
configuration.
	   American National Power is a Private Energy Producer (PEP) that
currently has 1,587MW operating in Texas. This will bring the total
capacity to 2,962MW with another 4,000MW in development.
	   International Power was created in 2000 by the break up of
National Power (London). International Power is one of the world's
leading independent electric generating companies with 850MW (net) in
operation with 2,350MW (net) under construction and another 8,000MW in
development.
	   Industrialinfo.com provides daily news related to the industrial
market place including industry alerts and databases for the energy
and industrial markets. For more information on trends and upcoming
construction activities for the energy and power markets as well as
other industrial sectors send inquiries to
powergroup@industrialinfo.com or visit us at www.industrialinfo.com
and www.iirenergy.com.

